This PR attempts to implement the suggestions in the PR #1184 by @rmackay9 to allow mavros to accept [POSITION_TARGET_GLOBAL_INT](https://mavlink.io/en/messages/common.html#POSITION_TARGET_GLOBAL_INT) message from FCU or GCS.

There were suggestions by @TSC21 and @vooon to implement a separate plugin for the purpose and use POSITION_TARGET_GLOBAL_INT message type.

There's an issue I found:

- After commanding the vehicle in off-board mode to a specific location, vehicle tends to go to a specific position(different from what it is commanded) everytime.

Hoping for a resolution to this issue.

pr_title: Tools: add ardupilot_gazebo to install-ROS-ubuntu script - WIP
pr_body:
This is a replacement for PR  https://github.com/ArduPilot/ardupilot/pull/21678 which adds gazebo to the AP-ROS install scripts.  This is all @snktshrma's work, I've raise the PR just to get over some merge issues.

The purpose of all of this of course is to make it easy to get AP and ROS running at least in SITL.
